PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1780419953
OL,3,CEleanor Donaldson 'did nothing'
OL,4,Cfollowing alleged abuse incident,
OL,5,Ccourt hears
OL,7,FShe said: "I think it is unfair to say
OL,8,Freally bad... his notes are his
OL,9,Finterpretation."
OL,11,FThe barrister then referred to an
OL,12,Fallegation made by Complainant A that
OL,13,Fon one occasion Donaldson had
OL,14,F"perched" over the top of her, using a
OL,15,Flight to look at her "private parts"
OL,16,Fwhen she was of secondary school age.
OL,18,FComplainant A said she had raised the
OL,19,Falleged abuse with Eleanor Donaldson
OL,20,Ffollowing the incident.
OL,26,@oD@KOUqD@PO]vD@AOUvD@IO]wD@VOUwD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
