OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1780419953
OL,3,CEleanor Donaldson 'did nothing'
OL,4,Cfollowing alleged abuse incident,
OL,5,Ccourt hears
OL,7,FComplainant A said this had happened
OL,8,Fon several occasions but there was one
OL,9,Fincident she had a "clear recollection
OL,10,Fof".
OL,12,FShe said she had told Eleanor
OL,13,FDonaldson about the incident and that
OL,14,Fit was "laughed off".
OL,16,FShe said: "That does not mean it was
OL,17,Flaughed off by me... I can absolutely
OL,18,Fguarantee you I was not laughing at
OL,19,Fall."
OL,26,@qD@TOUrD@CO]vD@HOUvD@TO]xD@KOU{D@EO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
